
Indexing is a technique used to speed up data retrieval by reducing the number of disk I/O operations.

An index is a type of data structure that stores:

Search Key	Data Reference
Key value	Pointer to disk block / record

Why Indexing?
Faster SELECT queries
Reduces disk access
Improves query performance

Indexing Methods
1. Primary Index (Clustering Index)
2. Secondary Index (Non-Clustering Index)

1ï¸âƒ£ Primary Indexing (Clustering Index)

A primary index is created when the data file is sorted on the search key.
The index order is the same as the data file order.

Data is stored sequentially on disk.

Dense vs Sparse Index in Primary Index
ğŸ”¹ Dense Index

Index entry for every search key value

More space required

